100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 26, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing global disarmament in light of rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the trial of John T. Scopes continued in Dayton, Tennessee, igniting fierce debates over evolution and education. Meanwhile, in Italy, Mussolini's government announced new measures to suppress dissent, tightening its grip on power as the country faced economic challenges.
